<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Glop Top Question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12384&amp;p=142923#p142923"><![CDATA[
Age can make those epoxy blobs very brittle.<br /><br />I had a copy of Super Momotaro Densetu for PC Engine, and cannibalized the case to make a nice case for my TG16 Everdrive, so I thought I'd take off the protective plastic on the Hu-Card and take a look at the chips under it.<br /><br />The act of bending the hu-card caused the epoxy blobs to literally disintegrate from the chip, leaving the bare silicon and wire bonding relatively unharmed.<br /><br />It was pretty cool.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5283">DNSDies</a> — Fri Mar 13, 2015 11:30 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
