<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12384&amp;p=141390#p141390"><![CDATA[
By the way the real name of this technology is &quot;Chip on board&quot;, not &quot;Glop Top&quot; and it's extremely widely used in mass-produced consummer electronics, not just NES cartridges.<br /><br />After too many units of a boards are produced, it's a waste of time and space to package all those chips when you could simply tie the chip to the board directly.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Feb 17, 2015 1:10 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
