<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12384&amp;p=141218#p141218"><![CDATA[
A bare silicon die. Wire bonding from the PCB to that die. Not much else.<br /><br />In NES cartridges, the epoxy blobs are usually ROMs, with the same wire bond order as the legs would have had.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Sat Feb 14, 2015 11:22 pm</p><hr />
